# raw 146 — prefix-length-mismatch-lint (stdlib starts_with helper gap)
@r146_raw_anchor hive/.raw L4845-4897 raw 146 (prefix-length-mismatch-lint, NEW 2026-04-28, severity warn)
@r146_issue_title "stdlib: starts_with(line: string, prefix: string) -> bool helper to retire substring(0, N) == literal off-by-one bug class"
@r146_minimal_reproducer_pointer hxc_migrate.hexa A15 _process_tree_decl (Phase 8 P8 closure doc) — pattern `if !(len(line) >= 8 && line.substring(0, 8) == '# tree:')` where '# tree:' is 7 chars not 8 → equality always false → ALL legitimate '# tree:' lines silently skipped
@r146_documented_at /Users/ghost/core/anima/docs/hxc_phase8_closure_20260428.md (Phase 8 P8 root-cause documentation)
@r146_failure_mode substring(start, end) where (end−start) ≠ len(literal_RHS) silently fails equality; static AST detection trivial; ad-hoc length math everywhere prefix comparison appears
@r146_proposed_signature stdlib_starts_with(line: string, prefix: string) -> bool /* ~10 LoC pure-hexa helper */
@r146_workaround_pattern_label starts_with (raw 159 NARROW lint matrix row 1) + substring-mismatch (matrix row 4)
