# raw 147 — prefix-aware-find-mandate (stdlib find_after helper gap)
@r147_raw_anchor hive/.raw L4899-... raw 147 (prefix-aware-find-mandate, NEW 2026-04-28, severity warn)
@r147_issue_title "stdlib: find_after(line: string, needle: string, start: int) -> int helper for prefix-skip semantics — first-match find() ignores prefix-skip intent in structured-format parsers"
@r147_minimal_reproducer_pointer hxc_migrate.hexa A15 _process_tree_decl — `let space_idx = line.find(' ')` on '# tree:0.A 2a62ba65:[...]' returns 1 (between '#' and 'tree:') NOT 10 (between '2a62ba65' and ':')
@r147_documented_at /Users/ghost/core/anima/docs/hxc_phase8_closure_20260428.md (Phase 8 P8 root-cause documentation)
@r147_audit_surface 813 hexa files use find(); 1462 total find call sites (서브에이전트 ae7c7e125 partial enumeration). Many likely OK (boolean / first-match-intended), but structured-format parsers are systematic-risk surface.
@r147_failure_mode line.find(needle) returns FIRST match index — when the prefix already contains the needle character (typical structured-format parsing), first-match semantics ignores prefix-skip intent → wrong split point → silent malformed parse
@r147_proposed_signature stdlib_find_after(line: string, needle: string, start: int) -> int /* ~15 LoC pure-hexa helper; returns -1 if not found at-or-after start */
